  "prompt": "Is it the Big Ongoing, not the Big Bang?",
  "response": "The term \"Big Bang\" refers to the prevailing cosmological theory about the origin of the universe, suggesting that it began as an extremely hot and dense point approximately 13.8 billion years ago and has been expanding ever since. The concept of the \"Big Ongoing\" doesn't replace the Big Bang, but rather emphasizes the continuous nature of cosmic expansion and evolution following the initial event. In this context, \"Big Ongoing\" could be seen as a way to highlight that the process initiated by the Big Bang is still unfolding today, as the universe continues to expand and change.",
